            >
            to seize Gaza City following PM Benjamin Netanyahu's
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-8-aug-25-spotlight-h2-8-announcement?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >announcement</a
            >
            that Israel intends to take full control of the Gaza Strip.
            Netanyahu says the full takeover is needed to eliminate Hamas,
            rescue hostages, secure Israel, and create a security perimeter. He
            insists Israel does not want to govern Gaza but plans to transfer
            control to a coalition of Arab states after the operation.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Hamas has called the plan a ‚Äúcoup‚Äù that sabotages ceasefire efforts.
            The UN, the UK, humanitarian groups, and some Israeli military
            leaders also oppose it, warning it could worsen the crisis. IDF
            Chief of Staff Lt. Gen. Eyal Zamir warned that the plan would
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-8-aug-25-spotlight-h2-9-endanger-hostages?source=website"
