        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>
              Summary: The US is facilitating domestic manufacturing of drugs
              and pressuring drugmakers to raise market value abroad.
            </strong>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            The USFDA has launched the
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-8-aug-25-spotlight-h3-12-fda-precheck-program?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >FDA PreCheck program</a
            >
            to expedite the approval of US-based manufacturing facilities,
            thereby boosting the domestic drug supply. It follows a two-phase
            approach: Phase One provides frequent communication with the FDA on
            facility design, construction, and pre-production. Phase Two
            provides pre-application meetings and early feedback to accelerate
            manufacturing and quality control development.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            The Trump administration has warned it could impose
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-8-aug-25-spotlight-h3-13-250-tariffs-on-pharmaceutical?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >250% tariffs on pharmaceutical</a
            >
            imports to encourage US-based manufacturing. Big drugmakers, like
            AstraZeneca and Johnson & Johnson, and Eli Lily will pledge billions
            to expand their US manufacturing operations and to build
            manufacturing plants. Trump had previously signed an
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-8-aug-25-spotlight-h3-14-executive-decree?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >executive decree</a
            >
            to boost domestic drug manufacturing and launched a similar
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-8-aug-25-spotlight-h3-15-voucher-based-program?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >voucher-based program</a
            >
            in June.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter: blur(5px)">
            Meanwhile, US officials have told pharmaceutical companies they‚Äôll
